outtro.p:
    Note that for x\geq {{start}}, we have that 




\displaystyle 0\leq 

    \frac{ \sqrt{ {{T11}} + {{T12}} + {{T14}} +{{T13}}  } }{  {{T21}} + {{T22}} + {{T24}} +{{T23}}   } \leq \frac{ \sqrt{ {{t11}} + {{t12}} + {{t14}} +{{t13}}  } }{ {{t21}} }


    \frac{  {{T11}} + {{T12}} + {{T14}} +{{T13}}   }{ \sqrt{  {{T21}} + {{T22}} + {{T24}} +{{T23}} }  }\leq \frac{  {{t11}} + {{t12}} + {{t14}} +{{t13}}   }{ \sqrt{ {{t21}} } }

= {{simp}}.  Thus \displaystyle \int_{ {{start }} }^\infty {{fx}}dx \leq \int_{ {{start }} }^\infty {{simp}}dx  which
converges since  {{P}} > 1 .  Thus \renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int_{ {{start }} }^\infty {{fx}}dx converges as well by the Comparison Theorem.




\displaystyle

    \frac{ \sqrt{ {{T11}} + {{T12}} + {{T14}} +{{T13}}  } }{  {{T21}} + {{T22}} + {{T24}} +{{T23}}   } \geq \frac{ \sqrt{ {{t11}} } }{ {{t21}} +{{t22}} +{{t24}} +{{t23}} }


    \frac{  {{T11}} + {{T12}} + {{T14}} +{{T13}}   }{ \sqrt{  {{T21}} + {{T22}} + {{T24}} +{{T23}} }  }\geq \frac{  {{t11}}   }{ \sqrt{ {{t21}} +{{t22}} + {{t24}} +{{t23}} } }

= {{simp}}\geq 0.  Thus \displaystyle \int_{ {{start }} }^\infty {{fx}}dx \geq \int_{ {{start }} }^\infty {{simp}}dx  which

diverges since  {{P}} \leq 1 .  Thus \renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int_{ {{start }} }^\infty {{fx}}dx diverges as well by the Comparison Theorem.
